Reasoning: The paper discusses a queueing network model that is commonly used in communication networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The study of scheduling policies and stability is also relevant to control systems (cs.SY). The analysis of the tail of the steady-state distribution and the expected steady-state backlog is related to probability and statistics (cs.PF) and the study of excursions of the maximum backlog over a finite time horizon is related to data structures (cs.DS).
